1. Trust Accounts

Under the Trust Act of Japan, trust activities must be ad- ministered separately from a commercial banking business. As a result, assets accepted in trust must be segregated from the assets held by SuMi TRUST Holdings. Within the general category of trust accounts, each trust account is segregated from other trust assets. Accordingly, the finane cial statements of SuMi TRUST Holdings do not reflect SuMi TRUST Holdings’ records as to the assets accepted in trust, which are maintained separately under the trust account.
